        <title type="html"><![CDATA[My Journey into Data Science — From Statistics to Machine Learning]]></title>
        <id>https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey</id>
        <link href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey"/>
        <updated>2025-06-01T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[When I first enrolled in the Statistics program at Universitas Gadjah Mada, I saw numbers as abstract concepts in textbooks. Four years later, I see them as stories waiting to be told — patterns hidden in noise, signals that can drive real-world decisions.]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>When I first enrolled in the Statistics program at Universitas Gadjah Mada, I saw numbers as abstract concepts in textbooks. Four years later, I see them as stories waiting to be told — patterns hidden in noise, signals that can drive real-world decisions.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="where-it-all-started">Where It All Started<a href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey#where-it-all-started" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Where It All Started" title="Direct link to Where It All Started" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>My journey began with traditional statistics — hypothesis testing, regression analysis, and probability theory. These fundamentals built a strong foundation, but it was when I discovered <strong>Python and machine learning</strong> that everything clicked. Suddenly, the statistical concepts I learned in class had powerful computational tools to bring them to life.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="the-turning-point">The Turning Point<a href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey#the-turning-point" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to The Turning Point" title="Direct link to The Turning Point" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Two experiences transformed my perspective:</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="1-leading-komunitas-satria-data-ugm">1. Leading Komunitas Satria Data UGM<a href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey#1-leading-komunitas-satria-data-ugm" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 1. Leading Komunitas Satria Data UGM" title="Direct link to 1. Leading Komunitas Satria Data UGM" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>As president of UGM's data community, I led a 27-member team and helped our university achieve <strong>4th place nationally in Satria Data 2024</strong>. Organizing study groups, workshops, and competition prep sessions taught me that data science is as much about <strong>collaboration and communication</strong> as it is about algorithms.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="2-my-internship-at-pt-bina-pertiwi-astra">2. My Internship at PT Bina Pertiwi (Astra)<a href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey#2-my-internship-at-pt-bina-pertiwi-astra" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 2. My Internship at PT Bina Pertiwi (Astra)" title="Direct link to 2. My Internship at PT Bina Pertiwi (Astra)" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>Working as a Data Analyst Intern at an Astra subsidiary was my first real taste of industry data work. Building real-time dashboards in Google Data Studio that actual stakeholders used for decision-making — that's when I understood the gap between academic projects and production-ready analytics.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="what-ive-learned">What I've Learned<a href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey#what-ive-learned" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What I've Learned" title="Direct link to What I've Learned" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>After 12+ projects, 6 competition awards, and 2 internships, here are my key takeaways:</p>
<ol>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Domain knowledge matters more than fancy algorithms.</strong> Understanding the business context transforms a good model into an impactful solution.</p>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Communication is a superpower.</strong> The best analysis is worthless if you can't explain it to non-technical stakeholders. Data storytelling is an essential skill.</p>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Start simple, iterate fast.</strong> My best-performing models often started as simple baselines. Complexity should be justified by results, not ego.</p>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>The data pipeline is 80% of the work.</strong> Data cleaning, preprocessing, and feature engineering consume far more time than model training — and they have a bigger impact on results.</p>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Open source and community are everything.</strong> Every project I've built stands on the shoulders of open-source tools and community knowledge.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="whats-next">What's Next<a href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/blog/data-science-journey#whats-next" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What's Next" title="Direct link to What's Next" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>I'm currently focused on deepening my expertise in:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>Deep learning</strong> for computer vision and NLP applications</li>
<li class=""><strong>MLOps</strong> for deploying and monitoring models in production</li>
<li class=""><strong>Statistical consulting</strong> for research and business applications</li>
</ul>
<p>If you're on a similar journey, feel free to reach out — I'm always happy to connect with fellow data enthusiasts.</p>
<hr>
<p><em>Thanks for reading! Browse my <a class="" href="https://fahmidza.github.io/myportfolio/docs/intro">project portfolio</a> to see these skills in action.</em></p>]]></content>
        <author>
            <name>Dzulfahmi Dzakia Ahmad</name>
